In `RenderContext.js`, the renderContext is always enabled by default with `this.clearColorValue = { r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 1 };`, making the `clear` method of the `WebGLBackend` always using that default value as the value is never getting updated when using `renderer.clear()`.

In the WebGLBackend, when calling `clear` it will always use `descriptor.clearColorValue` which is default to alpha = 1:
```js
if ( descriptor.clearColorValue ) {

clearColor = descriptor.clearColorValue;

} else {

clearColor = this.getClearColor();

// premultiply alpha

clearColor.r *= clearColor.a;
clearColor.g *= clearColor.a;
clearColor.b *= clearColor.a;

}
```

